FBIS4-18526 "drweu066_q_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 TURKEY Demirel: Albania `Trusted Partner' Demirel: Albania `Trusted Partner' TA0504185494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 GMT 5 Apr 94 TA0504185494 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Excerpt] Albanian President Sali Berisha, who is in Turkey on an official visit, has participated in a luncheon given in his honor by President Suleyman Demirel at the Cankaya Mansion. At the luncheon, Demirel said that Bulgarian-Turkish relations have reached a level that can serve as an example to the region and to the rest of the world. Demirel expressed Turkey's concern regarding the tragic and inhuman situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina spreading to Kosovo, Sandzak, and Vojvodina and indicated that he has been constantly warning concerned countries and international organization about this issue. [Begin Demirel recording] Turkey is making efforts to establish democracy, peace, and stability in the Balkans. We vehemently oppose coerced border changes and genocide with an aim to form ethnically pure countries. We view Albania, which shares our views and has a significant place in the region, as a true friend and a trusted partner in establishing peace and stability in the Balkans. [end recording] [passage omitted]
